About the job
About Us

Indie Campers, the go-to campervan Marketplace, is on a mission of making road trips available to everyone. Thanks to its digital approach and customer-centric orientation, Indie Campers has developed a strong booking experience and high-quality road trips at affordable prices.

With over one million nights rented through our travel platform, we have welcomed more than 300,000 travelers from 169 countries. We offer a comprehensive and expanding array of road trip possibilities: short-term RV rentals, long-term campervan subscriptions, and the possibility of buying one of our vehicles available for sale.

Rooted in a deep technological focus, our challenges are both exciting and demanding and require top talent and motivation to be successfully pursued. We are growing our team and looking for those interested in pursuing this dream with us and joining an ever-developing journey.

THE ROLE

We are looking for university students who are seeking genuine work experience, vocational placement or an internship located in our Depot in Bergen.

As an Indie Campers International Operations Intern, you'll be representing our brand in person, providing our guests with world-class customer service when they start and finish road trips of a lifetime. Do you enjoy challenges, meeting new people and fast-paced environments? If so, this position might be your next step!

THE INDIE COMMITMENT!

All internships are paid, the amount being dependent on location, country, and region (accommodation not included);
Continuous training and coaching to develop relevant skills to your growth: namely guest relations, customer service, problem solving, communication, team spirit, organisation, time management, work under pressure, fleet management, supplies management and logistics;
International opportunities and real chance of integration in Indie Campers after the internship, either in Field Operations or in a HQ role, in Lisbon or Los Angeles. 

WHO ARE WE LOOKING FOR?

You are a student in Hospitality, Tourism, International Studies, Business Administration, or a related field looking for an internship (mandatory to be enrolled in a university);
You are fluent in English, have a work permit and a valid driver's licence (mandatory);
You are available for a part-time or full-time internship: 25 or 40h per week, respectively, with working hours from 9:00 to 18:00;
You like international environments and meeting new cultures;
You have a natural talent for connecting with people and have a strong customer service orientation;
You are a problem solver who thrives on creating solutions and is not afraid to get their hands dirty. 

WHAT WILL YOU WORK ON?

Client relationship management: handle incoming reservations, register guests, process payments, explain the vehicle functionalities, as well as terms & conditions, and take care of check-ins and check-outs;
Operations management: align the reservations with the available campervans, prepare campervans;
Quality Control: maintain our campervans in top condition and monitor maintenance and repairing needs;
Stock management: monitor stock, restock, and process payments;
On-trip Assistance: handle clients' needs and troubleshooting emergencies. 

INTERNSHIP OPTIONS:

Minimum of 3 months and up to 12 months internship (flexible according to students´ availability).

Apply now!

Are you ready to Go Indie?

About the job
Company Description

Join Our Team as a Procurement Assistant!

DCS Noway is a fast-growing company and has been established since 2021 following multiple highly successful data center projects in Norway. Our team consists of local technical experts and is bolstered by international engineers. All our staff are experienced within the data center, heavy industrial, and high voltage industries.

Job Description

As a part of our Business Management team, you will be responsible for the following tasks:

Arrange and coordinate travel logistics, including booking cars, accommodations, and flights for employees as per company guidelines;
 Act as a point of contact with various Norwegian organizations such as DSB, NVE, UDI, and others, to facilitate necessary communication and compliance;
Manage incoming and outgoing mail, including opening, scanning, and taking appropriate action as needed;
Create compelling presentations with input from various teams, ensuring accuracy and professionalism;
Assist in project-related tasks, including document formatting, procurement support, and paperwork related to agreements with suppliers;
Organize and maintain company documents and systems, ensuring easy access and retrieval of information;
Assist with resolving basic IT issues and contribute to streamlining IT processes within the office;
Purchase necessary equipment for onboarding new employees, ensuring that they have the tools they need to succeed;
Maintain a record of company assets in Norway, including tracking, maintenance, and disposal when necessary;

Qualifications

To be successful you'll need:

Candidates must be Oslo Based
Bachelor's degree in business administration or related field preferred;
Proficiency in Microsoft Office(Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook);
Proven experience in administrative roles;
Native-level fluency in both written and spoken English;
Knowledge of Norwegian is a plus;
Familiarity with procurement processes is a plus;
Exceptional written communication skills, capable of compiling and presenting comprehensive reports with strong attention to detail;
Willingness to adopt a flexible approach to working hours and arrangements to accommodate project needs;
Great project management and management skills;
Self-motivated individual with strong teamwork abilities;
Creative and innovative mindset, capable of thinking outside the box;
Positive and flexible attitude, committed to completing tasks effectively;
Excellent organizational and time-management skills;
Effective communication and interpersonal abilities;
Ability to work independently and as part of a team;
Familiarity with procurement processes is a plus;

Additional Information

What we offer :

Good and competitive salary among the market;
Health Insurance and Benefits;
Be a part of a fast-growing company that has been established since 2021 following multiple highly successful data center projects with offices both in Portugal and Norway;

Joining our team you will have the opportunity to work independently and collaborate with a dynamic team on major data center projects. Apply your expertise and make a lasting impact on our clients' success!

DCS Norway is committed to fairness and inclusivity. Research tells us that applicants tend to only apply when they feel they meet 100% of the criteria. If you believe you have what it takes and this role excites you, but you don’t align perfectly with the criteria listed, we encourage you to still apply. We’d love to have a discussion!

About the job
OUR HIRING PROCESS:

We will review your application against our job requirements. We do not employ machine learning technologies during this phase as we believe every human deserves attention from another human. We do not think machines can evaluate your application quite like our seasoned recruiting professionals—every person is unique. We promise to give your candidacy a fair and detailed assessment. 
We may then invite you to submit a video interview for the review of the hiring manager. This video interview is often followed by a test or short project that allows us to determine whether you will be a good fit for the team. 
At this point, we will invite you to interview with our hiring manager and/or the interview team. Please note: We do not conduct interviews via text message, Telegram, etc. and we never hire anyone into our organization without having met you face-to-face (or via Zoom). You will be invited to come to a live meeting or Zoom, where you will meet our INFUSEmedia team. 
From there on, it's decision time! If you are still excited to join INFUSE and we like you as much, we will have a conversation about your offer. We do not make offers without giving you the opportunity to speak with us live. After all, we consider our team members our family, and we want you to feel comfortable and welcomed. 

Are you passionate about marketing? Ready to dive into the world of demand generation? INFUSEmedia is one of the fastest growing lead generation companies! INFUSED with drive, innovation, and integrity,

we craft demand solutions with precision to fuel our clients' pipelines, every time.

We are always looking for bright, motivated people to join our team. Apply now and tap into INFUSEmedia's growth!

INFUSEmedia is a truly global organization, with team members currently located in eight time zones (and quickly expanding). If you can work in any time zone from GMT to PST and have what it takes to win, we'd love to chat.

You will:

Help the Marketing Analyst Manager with various tasks;

Perform analysis and spreadsheet-based analytics to help the sales team determine and secure the campaign criteria, deliverable volumes, and pricing;

Perform research on upcoming proposals, market trends, products, and services provisions to better understand clients' needs

Make suggestions on upcoming and current campaign strategies;

Perform other duties as assigned.

To be successful, you need to be/have:

Uncompromising attention to detail and accuracy;

Excellent organizational and planning skills;

Great analytical skills;

Ability to work on multiple projects simultaneously, many under tight deadlines;

Extremely flexible and adaptive to changing circumstances;

Excellent communication skills.

About the job
About Textron GSE
Textron Ground Support Equipment, a division of Textron Specialized Vehicles Inc. is a leading global manufacturer of ground support equipment. Textron GSE markets products under the Safeaero, TUG, Douglas, and Premier brands. Textron GSE offers a full product line-up from conventional and towbarless pushbacks, baggage tractors, tow tractors, belt loaders, one-man and two-man deicers, ground power units, air starts, and air conditioning units. For more information, visit www.TextronGSE.com.
About Textron Specialized Vehicles
Textron Specialized Vehicles Inc. is a leading global manufacturer of golf cars, utility and personal transportation vehicles, snowmobiles, side-by-side terrain vehicles, professional turf-care equipment, and ground support equipment. Textron Specialized Vehicles markets products under several different brands. It's vehicles are found in environments ranging from golf courses to factories, airports to communities, and theme parks to hunting preserves.
Opportunity
We are seeking a Service Technician who will be responsible for the repair, maintenance, servicing, and commissioning of Safeaero equipment. You will be based in or around Oslo, however due to the nature and responsibilities of the role, you should expect to travel for up to 150 days of the year. Textron Sweden AB (based in Trelleborg, Sweden) develops, produces and supplies Safeaero de-icing vehicles to customers all over the world. As a Service Technician, you are an ambassador for the Company and have a responsibility to solve any issues the customers encounter (along with support from colleagues).
Responsibilities include, but are not limited to:
- Carrying out service work for customers, i.e. at airports and for airlines across Europe;
- Being responsible for the repair, maintenance, servicing, and commissioning of Safeaero equipment;
- Responsibility for the final configuration and testing of vehicles before they are sent to the end customer;
- Supporting customers and in-house departments, including Engineering and Sales;
- Providing technical support to customers and in-house colleagues, and communicating with staff at all levels;
- Travelling to customer sites;
- Ensuring guidelines and standards of work expected by Textron Sweden AB are understood and met;
- Ensuring follow up work requirements are referred to the appropriate departments within Textron Sweden to enable necessary action and recommendations to clients;
- Maintaining a professional approach and manner at all times, consistent with customer and Company expectations;
- Setting a good example to colleagues by observing and obeying all Company rules and regulations, complying with all site regulations, and safeguarding Company property;
- Setting a good example to colleagues by completing all necessary Company documentation punctually and in accordance with any guidelines or schedules issued (including staff expenses claims, site reports, etc.);
- Attending all training courses and meetings as required by Textron Sweden AB;
- Providing support and co-operation to management and colleagues;
- Being prepared and willing to help and contribute to the success of the company at all times;
- Observing and adhering to Company Health and Safety guidelines.
Desired Skills and Experience
- You should have a technical qualification (e.g. in Engineering);
- System knowledge and an understanding of hydraulics, pneumatics, electrics, and the ability to read drawings;
- Ability to give technical direction and product training;
- You must be willing to travel, which could include up to 150 days with customers;
- Experience of engaging with customers in a pressurized environment;
- You should be able to read and understand electrical/mechanical/hydraulic/pneumatic drawings and diagrams;
- Ability to document your work;
- Competent with MS Office, and able to upload and download specialist software;
- Commercial awareness and an ability to communicate at all levels regarding technical matters;
- Ability to prioritise takes effectively, and to work under pressure.

About the job
A global provider of highly innovative infotainment products that make every screen an opportunity is looking for a Platform Engineer. Its range of award-winning, fully integrated, low-footprint digital media offerings combine high performance with high quality and are truly system agnostic. Whether embedded, as mobile apps or through the cloud, supports all digital media scenarios for any industry and any device. Its product portfolio is designed and built to deliver excellence, accelerate time to market, and lower TCO for its clients while creating digital media experiences that matter.

As a Platform Engineer you will be part of the team responsible for the environments hosting development and production services.

You will work closely with Software Engineers and Quality Assurance Engineers to provide tooling for automated deployments and testing in order to facilitate and ensure the consistent delivery of high-quality infotainment solutions in the cloud.

This position implies relocation to Germany or Hungary.

Responsibilities:

Design, deploy and manage scalable multi-stage cloud-based environments covering the lifecycle of our services from development to production; 
Monitoring and reporting for these environments; 
Support development and QA teams to find the best solutions and ways to solve problems for cloud-based services; 
Diagnose issues and improve the efficiency and reliability of these services; 
Participation in the on-call duty rota of the 24/7 operations. 

Experience & Skills:

At least 5 years’ experience in managing cloud-based online services (AWS, Azure); 
Significant experience in running services in Kubernetes-based environments (AKS, EKS, Docker); 
Ability to program in one or more high level languages (Golang, Python, JavaScript); 
Knowledge of automated deployment and infrastructure management processes (terraform flux, ansible, Jenkins); 
Understanding of the main Observability principles; 
Self-motivated and proactive mindset, ability to work under minimal supervision; 
Ability and willingness to work collaboratively within a team and with colleagues in other departments; 
Good written and verbal English skills. 

Conditions:

Friendly team; 
Interesting projects; 
Work in an office in Budapest or Karlsruhe; 
Relocation to Budapest or Karlsruhe is possible.

